{"parse":{"title":"Introducing Relativity","pageid":53155382,"revid":826472094,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Introducing Relativity <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introducing+Relativity&amp;rft.author=Bruce+Bassett&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books+%28UK%29%3Cbr+%2F%3ETotem+Books+%28US%29&amp;rft.series=%5B%5BIntroducing...+book+series%7CIntroducing...%5D%5D\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:IntroducingRelativity.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"IntroducingRelativity.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/IntroducingRelativity.jpg/220px-IntroducingRelativity.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a4/IntroducingRelativity.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"257\" data-file-height=\"386\" /></a><div>First edition cover</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\nBruce Bassett</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Illustrator</th><td>\nRalph Edney</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited Kingdom</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Series</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Introducing..._book_series\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Introducing... book series\">Introducing...</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Theory_of_relativity\" title=\"Theory of relativity\">Relativity</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Albert_Einstein\" title=\"Albert Einstein\">Albert Einstein</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nIcon Books (UK)<br />Totem Books (US)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n2002</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1840463724\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1840463724\">1840463724</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Introducing Relativity</b></i> is a 2002 <a href=\"/wiki/Graphic_novel\" title=\"Graphic novel\">graphic</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Study_guide\" title=\"Study guide\">study guide</a> to the <a href=\"/wiki/Theory_of_relativity\" title=\"Theory of relativity\">theory of relativity</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Albert_Einstein\" title=\"Albert Einstein\">Albert Einstein</a> written by Bruce Bassett and illustrated by Ralph Edney. The volume is, according to the publisher's website, \"a superlative, fascinating graphic account of Einstein\u2019s strange world,\" which, \"plots a visually accessible course through the thought experiments that have given shape to contemporary physics.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-IB01_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-IB01-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>\"The authors cover everything from <a href=\"/wiki/Time_dilation\" title=\"Time dilation\">time dilation</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/Black_holes\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Black holes\">black holes</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/String_theory\" title=\"String theory\">string theory</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/Dark_energy\" title=\"Dark energy\">dark energy</a>,\" confirms <i><a href=\"/wiki/Sky_at_Night_Magazine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sky at Night Magazine\">Sky at Night Magazine</a></i> reviewer Professor <a href=\"/wiki/Nigel_Henbest\" title=\"Nigel Henbest\">Nigel Henbest</a>, and, \"the going sometimes gets tough.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-SN01_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SN01-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> However, \"help is at hand,\" according to <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Scientist\" title=\"New Scientist\">New Scientist</a></i> reviewer <a href=\"/wiki/Marcus_Chown\" title=\"Marcus Chown\">Marcus Chown</a>, \"to get our heads around stretchy time, shrinking space, black holes, wormholes and the rest.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NS01_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NS01-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publication_history\">Publication history</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Introducing_Relativity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Publication history\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>This volume was originally published in the UK by Icon Books and in the US by Totem Books in 2002, and subsequently republished with different covers and the subtitle, <i>A Graphic Guide</i>.\n</p><p>Selected editions:\n</p>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\"><i>Introducing Relativity</i>. Icon Books. 2002. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1840463724\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1840463724\">1840463724</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introducing+Relativity&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.isbn=1840463724&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\"><i>Introducing Relativity</i>. Icon Books. 2006. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1840467576\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1840467576\">1840467576</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introducing+Relativity&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=1840467576&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\"><i>Introducing Relativity: A Graphic Guide</i>. Icon Books. 2012. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1848310579\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1848310579\">1848310579</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introducing+Relativity%3A+A+Graphic+Guide&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=1848310579&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<p>Related volumes in the series:\n</p>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Schwartz, Joseph; McGuinness, Michael (1992). <i><a href=\"/wiki/Einstein_for_Beginners\" title=\"Einstein for Beginners\">Einstein for Beginners</a></i>. Icon Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1874166021\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1874166021\">1874166021</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Einstein+for+Beginners&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=1874166021&amp;rft.aulast=Schwartz&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rft.au=McGuinness%2C+Michael&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Rankin, William (1993). <i><a href=\"/wiki/Newton_for_Beginners\" title=\"Newton for Beginners\">Newton for Beginners</a></i>. Icon Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1863734953\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1863734953\">1863734953</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Newton+for+Beginners&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.isbn=1863734953&amp;rft.aulast=Rankin&amp;rft.aufirst=William&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Felix, Pirani; Christina, Roche (1993). <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Universe_for_Beginners\" title=\"The Universe for Beginners\">The Universe for Beginners</a></i>. Icon Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1874166064\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1874166064\">1874166064</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Universe+for+Beginners&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.isbn=1874166064&amp;rft.aulast=Felix&amp;rft.aufirst=Pirani&amp;rft.au=Christina%2C+Roche&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">McEvoy, J.P.; Z\u00e1rate, Oscar (1995). <i>Stephen Hawking for Beginners</i>. Icon Books.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Stephen+Hawking+for+Beginners&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.aulast=McEvoy&amp;rft.aufirst=J.P.&amp;rft.au=Z%C3%A1rate%2C+Oscar&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">McEvoy, J.P.; Z\u00e1rate, Oscar (1996). <i>Quantum Theory for Beginners</i>. Icon Books.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Quantum+Theory+for+Beginners&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.aulast=McEvoy&amp;rft.aufirst=J.P.&amp;rft.au=Z%C3%A1rate%2C+Oscar&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Callender, Craig; Edney, Ralph (2001). <i>Introducing Time</i>. Icon Books.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introducing+Time&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.aulast=Callender&amp;rft.aufirst=Craig&amp;rft.au=Edney%2C+Ralph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Clegg, Brian; Pugh, Oliver (2012). <i>Introducing Infinity</i>. Icon Books.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introducing+Infinity&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.aulast=Clegg&amp;rft.aufirst=Brian&amp;rft.au=Pugh%2C+Oliver&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Whyntie, Tom; Pugh, Oliver (2013). <i>Introducing Particle Physics</i>. Icon Books.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introducing+Particle+Physics&amp;rft.pub=Icon+Books&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.aulast=Whyntie&amp;rft.aufirst=Tom&amp;rft.au=Pugh%2C+Oliver&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Introducing_Relativity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Marcus_Chown\" title=\"Marcus Chown\">Marcus Chown</a>, writing in <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Scientist\" title=\"New Scientist\">New Scientist</a></i>, describes the volume as, \"a very attractive illustrated guide to arguably the greatest ever achievement by a single human mind,\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NS01_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NS01-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> which, according to Professor <a href=\"/wiki/Nigel_Henbest\" title=\"Nigel Henbest\">Nigel Henbest</a>, writing in <i><a href=\"/wiki/Sky_at_Night_Magazine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sky at Night Magazine\">Sky at Night Magazine</a></i>, \"has all the answers you need.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-SN01_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SN01-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Science writer <a href=\"/wiki/Brian_Clegg_(writer)\" title=\"Brian Clegg (writer)\">Brian Clegg</a>, author of <i>Introducing Infinity</i> (2012) in the same series, however finds the book, \"good on content, not so good on bringing it down to the right level.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-PS01_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-PS01-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>\"Cosmologist Bruce Bassett and mathematician-cartoonist Ralph Edney are awe-inspiring,\" according to Henbest, \"in their attempts at a popular explanation of one of the most daunting areas of science.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-SN01_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SN01-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  Chown states that the \"remarkable amount of material,\" touched on by the writers goes, \"from inertia to the theory of inflation; from singularity theorems to superstring theory; from unification to accelerating universes.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NS01_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NS01-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> However, Clegg speculates that Bassett's background as a lecturer in cosmology lecturer, \"is reflected in the fact there is rather more cosmology in this book than a pure explanation of relativity would require,\" and in that it, \"is much stronger on the theory than the history.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-PS01_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-PS01-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>\"Unfortunately for a book that appears to be aimed at the absolute beginner,\" states Clegg, \"there are parts that are roughly equivalent to material in the first year of a degree course.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-PS01_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-PS01-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \"It helps if you have a passing familiarity with some of the concepts,\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NS01_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NS01-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> agrees Chown, and, \"you\u2019d probably need A-level physics to absorb all of the concepts fully,\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-SN01_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SN01-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> confirms Henbest. \n</p><p>\"Overall,\" concludes Clegg, \"it's a noble attempt, with much (much) more meat in it than the companion Introducing Chaos book - but it would need more historical perspective and less inclination to jump to soon into formulae if it were to appeal to its target audience.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-PS01_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-PS01-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Nonetheless, according to Henbest, \"the format means it\u2019s an easy book to dip into, making cutting-edge science available to everyone,\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-SN01_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SN01-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and according to Chown, \"anyone with an enquiring mind is bound to take away something as they dip in and out of this highly entertaining book.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NS01_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NS01-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Introducing_Relativity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-IB01-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-IB01_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.introducingbooks.com/title/introducing-relativity/\">\"Introducing Relativity: A Graphic Guide\"</a>. <i>Icon Books</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-01-20</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Icon+Books&amp;rft.atitle=Introducing+Relativity%3A+A+Graphic+Guide&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.introducingbooks.com%2Ftitle%2Fintroducing-relativity%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntroducing+Relativity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SN01-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-SN01_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-SN01_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-SN01_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-SN01_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-SN01_2-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Henbest, Nigel. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.skyatnightmagazine.com/book/astrophysics/relativity-graphic-guide\">\"Rela